        <h2>Welcome to the Open Source Job Portal</h2>
        <p>
            The Open Source Job Portal is a dynamic web application designed to connect job seekers with job listings from various employers. Our mission is to create an accessible platform that allows users to find job opportunities easily while also enabling employers to post job listings effectively.
        </p>
        <h3>Project Goals</h3>
        <p>
            This project aims to provide students with practical experience in building a full-stack application using both frontend and backend technologies. Students will have the opportunity to learn about:
        </p>
        <ul>
            <li>Implementing user authentication for job seekers and employers.</li>
            <li>Managing job listings and applications.</li>
            <li>Using modern web development technologies.</li>
            <li>Working on an open-source project and contributing to the community.</li>
        </ul>
        <h3>Features</h3>
        <p>
            The Open Source Job Portal includes several key features to enhance the user experience:
        </p>
        <ul>
            <li>User registration and authentication for both job seekers and employers.</li>
            <li>Job listing creation, management, and application functionalities.</li>
            <li>Advanced job search and filtering options.</li>
            <li>A responsive design for accessibility on various devices.</li>
            <li>Open-source contribution opportunities for developers.</li>
        </ul>
        <h3>Get Involved</h3>
        <p>
            We welcome contributions from the community! Whether you are a developer, designer, or simply interested in helping out, there are many ways to get involved in the Open Source Job Portal project. Join us in building a platform that makes job searching easier for everyone.
